We’re making a map about the racial demographics of Harris County, Texas.

load_variables(2018, "acs5") |> filter(concept=="RACE")

# saving the names of variables related to race, in this order
# white, Black, Asian, Hispanic
# weird that we are just choosing these four and ignoring people who are biracial
racevars <- c(White="B02001_002", 
              Black="B02001_003", 
              Asian="B02001_005", 
              Hispanic="B03003_003")
county_data <- get_acs(geography = "tract",
        variables = racevars,
        year = 2018, 
        state = "Illinois",
        county = "Cook",
        geometry = TRUE,
        summary_var = "B02001_001") |> 
    mutate(Percent = estimate/summary_est * 100)

county_data |> 
  ggplot(aes(fill=Percent,
         color = Percent)) +
  facet_wrap(~variable) + 
  scale_fill_viridis_c(direction=-1)+
  scale_color_viridis_c(direction=-1)+
  theme_void() + 
  labs(title="Racial geography of Cook County, IL",
       caption = "Source: American Community Survey 2014-2018",
       variable = c("x","y","z","v"),
       B02001_002 = "xx") +
  geom_sf()
